Title: Catching Fire (The Hunger Games, #2)
Author: Suzanne Collins
My Review:
4.5
Wow this book was a roller coaster of emotions, mostly sad. I absolutely love Katniss this is the complex female character a 16 year old girl forced to grow up who makes mistakes, is taken advantage of but at the end of the day she’s a good person who will do anything for the people she loves.
Peeta has my whole heart such an inherently good character.
President Snow is definitely a very evil, cunning and one the most intresting character that I have ever read.

Title: Sunrise on the Reaping (The Hunger Games, #0.5)
Author: Suzanne Collins
My Review:
4.5

This book really explains Haymitch's alcoholism. This book really felt like the last piece of a puzzle.Suzanne Collins uses this story to really drive home the fact that actual villain is and will always be Snow and the Capitol. Also what's with Snow and his tendency to wage psychological warfare against teenagers like didn't the man have a country to run.

My Review: The book had a captivating plot but the only problem for me was pacing.

Title: A Curse for True Love (Once Upon a Broken Heart, #3)
Author: Stephanie Garber
My Review:
3.5 stars
Finally Jacks gets his happy ending!!
But there are a lot of plot that wasn't uncovered. Like what was LaLa's story with Dane? What happens to Chaos? Where the hell is Marisol? What does Jacks eat apples all the time? What about the third kiss Evangeline owed him? What happened to Luc?What happened to Apollo’s brother and his rebellion army? I didn't get a few answers I wanted. There were a LOT of loose ends but u still enjoyed the story

Title: The Ballad of Songbirds and Snakes (The Hunger Games, #0)
Author: Suzanne Collins
My Review:
4.5 stars

Suzanne Collins is such a genius writer.
She made me feel almost bad for Snow but by the end of it he turned into the worst version of himself. I absolutely loved this book and how it ties up the whole Hunger Games Series. Also District 12 girls have my heart. So smart and stubborn always defying Capitol on their own way.
I remember reading the whole hunger games and thought Snow is definitely one of the most intresting characters. From the not so innocent Coryo to absolutely evil mastermind President Coriolanus Snow what a journey!!

Title: Mockingjay (The Hunger Games, #3)
Author: Suzanne Collins
My Review:
“We burn, You burn with us”
There are no winners in a war, only survivors.

Title: The Hunger Games (The Hunger Games, #1)
Author: Suzanne Collins
My Review:
I read this book when I was 15 years old but I couldn’t remember much of it, I wanted to read “The Ballad Of Songbirds And Snakes”.I did remember enjoying it even back then but I couldn’t really understand what sort of rebellion Katniss had started but rereading it at almost 20 feels like a whole different experience.

Katniss and Peeta have something that’s so genuine even if she doesn’t understand it completely. I absolutely admire Katniss for her courage. The writing is so well done everything is said so seamlessly and subtly because I recognised so many references that would come up in the next book. The games in itself was such a horrific tale. Even characters you were supposed to hate I couldn’t because they were raised to believe that this horrific game was a good thing.

Overall I’m so glad I decided to reread this.

Author: Prajakta Koli

1.5 stars
The writing in this book was one of the worst things i have ever read, the plot was mid but the wanna be genz slangs were too much. I’ve read wattpad books with better writing. It was a very wanna be American novel. The main female character was very annoying which made this book even more tedious to read. The main male lead is a one dimensional character with no character development whatsoever. Also how did a 23 year old post graduate law student have so much time on her hand? It’s absolutely ridiculous
